# Keep LF line endings in the repo AND on checkout on every platform.
#
# Rationale: hooks/*.js are ESM modules that begin with a `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang. On Windows,
# Git's default (autocrlf=true) would check them out with CRLF, which (a) breaks importing them in
# the test suite — vite's shebang transform throws "SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token" — and
# (b) breaks the shebang for POSIX execution. Forcing LF eliminates the whole class of cross-platform
# line-ending bugs. Files are already stored LF, so this introduces no renormalization diff.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending-normalized.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
